Fix SLANT, WEIGHT, WIDTH properties to accept range values

Modern fontconfig (2.13+) writes range values like [0 200) for the
weight/width/slant properties in system font caches. Fontconfig 2.12.x
declares these as FcTypeInteger which rejects range values, causing
crashes when reading system caches on newer distributions.

Change these to FcTypeRange (matching what fontconfig 2.13.0+ does).
FcTypeRange objects already accept integer and double values through
FcObjectValidType, so this is backwards compatible.

diff --git a/src/fcobjs.h b/src/fcobjs.h
--- a/src/fcobjs.h
+++ b/src/fcobjs.h
@@ -29,9 +29,9 @@
 FC_OBJECT (FULLNAME,		FcTypeString,	NULL)
 FC_OBJECT (FULLNAMELANG,	FcTypeString,	NULL)
-FC_OBJECT (SLANT,		FcTypeInteger,	FcCompareNumber)
-FC_OBJECT (WEIGHT,		FcTypeInteger,	FcCompareNumber)
-FC_OBJECT (WIDTH,		FcTypeInteger,	FcCompareNumber)
+FC_OBJECT (SLANT,		FcTypeRange,	FcCompareSizeRange)
+FC_OBJECT (WEIGHT,		FcTypeRange,	FcCompareSizeRange)
+FC_OBJECT (WIDTH,		FcTypeRange,	FcCompareSizeRange)
 FC_OBJECT (SIZE,		FcTypeRange,	FcCompareSizeRange)
 FC_OBJECT (ASPECT,		FcTypeDouble,	NULL)
